summary.narrativeincludeclinical:
Initial information received on 13 Dec 2006 via consumer's attorney in form of a civil complaint (case # 06 CV 14180): Attorney alleged that the consumer (plaintiff) was injected with Zometa (zoledronate) for an unspecified duration and indication. She then developed osteonecrosis of the jaw. As a result of administration of the drug she suffered severe physical and medical injuries and associated disabilities including severe pain and suffering, severe mental anguish, and the loss of enjoyment of life.
Follow-up information received from the consumer's attorney on 16 Jun 2010 inclusive of medical and laboratory records. The patient received Zometa, Aredia (pamidronate disodium) and Femara (letrozole) from an unknown date and for an unspecified indication. She was diagnosed with breast carcinoma in Jul 1998. Medical records dated 23 Aug 1999 noted that the patient's medical history included breast lumpectomy in Jul 1998 for breast cancer. Medical records dated 19 Apr 2000 noted that the patient had Stage IIIA breast cancer and depression. Laboratory records dated 02 Jan 2001 noted that the PET scan performed on 22 Dec 2000 revealed evidence of metastatic disease in T11, T12, L2, L4 and S1 and single left posterior rib. The PET scan impression was wide spread skeletal metastases-asymptomatic. Medical records dated 31 Jan 2001 noted that the patient had recurrent breast cancer and was advised to continue Femara and Aredia. Medical records dated 07 Nov 2001 noted that the patient had Stage IV breast cancer. Medical records dated 01 May 2002 noted that the patient had left elbow pain- probably tendonitis and was advised to continue Zometa and Femara. Medical records dated 29 Oct 2002 noted that the patient had Urinary tract infection, frequent urination and burning urination. Medical records dated 02 Oct 2003 noted that the patient had fatigue and wheezing. She was diagnosed with acute bronchitis, progressive metastatic breast carcinoma and metastatic bone carcinoma. Medical records dated 03 Nov 2003 noted that the patient had sinus infection, headache and tooth pain. Medical records dated 25 Sep 2007 noted that the patient had shortness of breath, fever, uncontrolled cough, mastoiditis, chest pain and uncontrolled nausea and vomiting.
Follow up received on 06 Jul 2010 from the consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Medical record dated 06 Feb 2005 indicated multiple abscesses of the maxilla and one within the mandible. Medical record dated 08 Jun 2006 indicated compression fractures. Medical record dated 24 Oct 2006 indicated stable partially calcified mediastinal and mesenteric enlarged lymph nodes. Medical record dated 27 Jun 2007 indicated interval progression in size and number of hepatic metastases. Medical record dated 24 Jul 2007 indicated a MRI of brain and brainstem revealed a 5 mm lesion in the right cerebellum and a second lesion in the occipital portion. Medical record dated 27 Aug 2007 indicated a small right pleural effusion, bilateral platelike atelectasis, abdomen distension, and severe degenerative disc disease. Medical record dated 27 Sep 2007 indicated the patient had an unchanged small right apical pneumothorax.
Follow-up report received on 12 Jul 2010 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Past medical history included CT scan of the chest on 26 Aug 1998 revealed the lungs were clear of infiltrates or effusions. No parenchyma nodules or masses were seen. No hilar or mediastinal adenopathy was identified. Conclusion noted no convincing radiographic evidence of acute or active intra-abdominal disease. Additional medical history included abdominal pain, fractured proximal phalanx of the fourth toe, lumpectomy followed by radiation therapy in the right breast in the interval. Records dated 29 Dec 2000 reported placement of a central venous catheter. No further information was provided.
Follow up received on 26 Jul 2010 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. On 20 Aug 2007, an X-ray was done due to vomiting which showed mild adynamic ileus. No further information was provided.
Follow up received on 02 Aug 2010 from the consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Medical record dated 01 Nov 2005 indicated the patient had cerebellar metastasis, hepatic metastasis, DVT several years ago and was prescribed with Lovenox; and mouth infection and ulcer infection; prescribed amoxicillin, nizoral and cipro. Additional concomitant medications were provided.
Follow up received on13 Sep 2010 from the consumers attorney inclusive of medical records: Medical records dated 24 Sep 2007 and 13 Nov 2007 indicated the patient had decreased appetite, weight loss, bilateral hip osteoarthritis and small vessel ischemia. The consumer's medical records also inclusive of updates of medical history and concomitant medications.
Follow-up received on 12 Nov 2010 via the consumer's attorney contained medical records. On 20 Jul 1998 the patient underwent right breast biopsy and was found to have invasive ductal carcinoma in situ, intermediate grade. Pathology diagnosed adenocarcinoma, metastatic. She underwent partial mastectomy 29 Jul 1998. Her chemotherapy included Navelbine (vinorelbine) and tamoxifen. The patient began receiving Zometa 4 mg IV every four weeks in 2003, and the infusion frequency was increased to every three weeks on 16 Sep 2003. While being treated with Zometa she experienced anemia which resolved with use of Aranesp (darbepoetin alfa). She was noted to have leukopenia and neutropenia on 28 Oct 2003.
Follow-up received on 17 Aug 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Record dated 02 Nov 2005 stated that the patient had exposed bone of the left mandible and sequestrum, left mandible. Record dated 10 Jul 2006 stated that the patient had sores in mouth and leg cramps. Record dated 24 Oct 2006 stated that the patient developed moderate central canal stenosis at L4. Records dated 25 Apr 2007 stated that the patient had granulomata within the spleen, scattered diverticula and atherosclerotic calcification of the abdominal aorta. Record dated 27 Jun 2007 stated that the patient had bibasilar pulmonary edema. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 03 Oct 2012, via consumer's attorney inclusive of the medical records. The patient's family history included pancreatic cancer (father) and hypertension (mother). The patient's concomitant medications included Paclitaxel, Cytoxan (cyclophosphamide) and Adriamycin (doxorubicin). Record dated 06 Feb 2005 stated that patient had otitis media, secondary malignant neoplasm of bone and bone marrow and embolism of vein. The records further stated that the patient underwent tooth extraction. Record dated 12 Mar 2005 stated that patient had agranulocytosis, secondary and unspecified malignant neoplasm of lymph nodes of axilla and upper limb, lesion in jaw and pitting edema to left lower extremity. On 27 Dec 2005, MRI of the left side of mandible revealed bone marrow edema. Record further stated that patient had inflammatory condition of jaw, soft tissue infection of left jaw, increasing left jaw pain, difficulty in chewing and osteomyelitis. The records further stated that, the patient underwent lymph node dissection and hormone therapy. Record dated 07 Jun 2006 stated that patient had spinal cord compression and osteoporosis. Record dated 08 Jun 2006 stated that patient had mild anterolisthesis of L3 on L4 and L4 on L5. Record dated 10 Jun 2006 noted lymphedema to right upper extremity. Record dated 27 Aug 2007 stated that patient had sclerosis of the left rib. Record dated 25 Sep 2007 stated that patient had dysthymic disorder. Chest x-ray performed on 26 Sep 2007 revealed right basilar lung nodule and healed rib fractures of 5, 6 and 7th ribs. Record dated 05 Nov 2007 stated that patient had secondary malignant neoplasm of pleura, hypercalcemia and splenic metastases. Record further stated that patient underwent back surgery and vertebroplasty. Record with unspecified date revealed that patient had pathological fracture of vertebra. The outcome of the event healed rib fractures of 5, 6 and 7th ribs was condition improving. The outcome of the other events was not reported.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 08 Oct 2012 inclusive of medical records: Record dated 20 Oct 2005, noted that the patient had degenerative changes in the lower lumber spine. Record dated 09 Oct 2007, stated that the patient was diagnosed with osteophyte formation in hip joints. Outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 05 Dec 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical record. The patient’s historical conditions included tonsillectomy and bilateral tubal ligation. The patient’s current condition included metastatic breast cancer. The patient was treated with Zometa for bone metastases from breast cancer. Record dated 17 Jul 2003 stated that the patient had one episode of minor hematemesis, facial and orbital edema. Record dated 13 Jul 2004 stated that patient had bladder dysfunction. Record dated 18 Jan 2005 stated that patient had gingivitis. Record dated 06 Feb 2005 stated that patient had caries involving the two most posterior left molars. Record dated 07 Feb 2005 stated that the patient had dental abscess. Record dated 21 Feb 2005 stated that patient underwent debridement for tooth abscess. Record dated 21 Mar 2005 stated that the patient had sepsis. Record dated 20 Oct 2005 stated that patient had infected tooth. Record dated 23 Mar 2006 stated that patient had lesions in her mouth. Record dated 02 May 2006 stated that patient had 0.5 cm nodule in the roof of her mouth which got resolved. Record dated 26 Jun 2006 stated that patient had L4 compression fracture. Record dated 15 Aug 2006 stated that patient had left mandibular osteonecrosis with on and off cellulitis in the area. Record dated 25 Apr 2007 stated that patient had fibrocystic changes in both the lungs. Record dated 30 Apr 2007 stated that patient had purulent material draining through the left mandible area and left mandible area wound on the outside. Record dated 30 Jul 2007 stated that patient had mandible bacterial colonization. Record dated 27 Aug 2007 stated that patient had small arachnoid cyst in the anterior aspect of the cisterna. The patient passed away on 28 Feb 2008. Outcome of the other events was not reported.
summary.sendercomment: Medical assessment: Review of available data reported in this legal case does not allow for proper causality assessments.
